# Facial Recognition-Based Attendance System  

## üë• Team Members & Roles  

This project is a collaborative effort by a team of five. Below are the roles and responsibilities assigned to each team member to ensure efficient development and execution.  

---

## üéØ Roles & Responsibilities  

### **1Ô∏è‚É£ Project Manager & System Architect (Team Lead)**  
**Responsibilities:**  
- Define the project scope, goals, and timeline.  
- Oversee team coordination and ensure tasks are completed on time.  
- Design the system architecture and ensure all components integrate smoothly.  
- Make critical technical decisions regarding frameworks, libraries, and tools.  
- Conduct security and privacy risk assessments.  
- Monitor overall project progress and resolve roadblocks.  

**Key Deliverables:**  
- System architecture diagram  
- Project roadmap and task allocation  
- Regular progress reports  

---

### **2Ô∏è‚É£ Frontend Developer (UI/UX Specialist)**  
**Responsibilities:**  
- Develop the **Lecturer Dashboard** and **Student Portal** using React.js.  
- Implement Material UI (MUI) components for a clean and user-friendly interface.  
- Ensure responsiveness and accessibility for different screen sizes.  
- Integrate frontend components with the backend API.  
- Work closely with the backend developer for seamless data exchange.  

**Key Deliverables:**  
- Responsive UI for the dashboard and attendance tracking  
- API integration with backend services  
- UI testing and bug fixes  

---

### **3Ô∏è‚É£ Backend Developer (API & Database Management)**  
**Responsibilities:**  
- Develop the backend server using **Node.js & Express.js**.  
- Design and implement **MongoDB** database schema.  
- Create RESTful APIs for user authentication, attendance sessions, and reporting.  
- Implement **OAuth & JWT authentication** for secure access.  
- Optimize database queries and ensure backend efficiency.  

**Key Deliverables:**  
- API endpoints documentation (Swagger/Postman)  
- Secure authentication and session management  
- Integration with facial recognition module  

---

### **4Ô∏è‚É£ AI/ML Engineer (Facial Recognition & Image Processing)**  
**Responsibilities:**  
- Develop the **Facial Recognition Module** using **OpenCV & TensorFlow/Keras**.  
- Train and fine-tune the model for accurate facial recognition.  
- Implement face detection, recognition, and anti-spoofing techniques.  
- Optimize AI model performance and handle dataset management.  
- Integrate the facial recognition system with backend attendance processing.  

**Key Deliverables:**  
- Trained AI model for facial recognition  
- Image preprocessing and model optimization scripts  
- Documentation on how to retrain the model with new student data  

---

### **5Ô∏è‚É£ DevOps & Security Engineer (Deployment & Maintenance)**  
**Responsibilities:**  
- Set up and configure **servers** for hosting the system.  
- Deploy the application using **Docker & Nginx** for scalability.  
- Implement **CI/CD pipelines** for automated testing and deployment.  
- Monitor system performance and handle security concerns (data encryption, GDPR compliance).  
- Ensure proper logging, error handling, and backups.  

**Key Deliverables:**  
- Deployed application
- CI/CD pipeline configuration for automated testing and deployment
- Security configuration documentation and compliance reports
- System monitoring dashboard and alert setup
- Backup and disaster recovery procedures
- Infrastructure-as-code (IaC) templates for environment replication



